Reasoning: The paper focuses on the design of biological networks using bacteria as the basic elements of the network, which involves the study of the transfer of information to the population by stimulating it with a concentration of special type of molecules signal. This falls under the category of multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of molecular communication and the investigation of the collective sensing capability of the node also suggest the possibility of the paper belonging to the categories of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), systems and control (cs.SY), and bioinformatics (cs.BIO).
